graphic territory.  Along with training you will have support from our Sales Management team to help identify, qualify and close new business on a quarterly basis.  On a daily basis ISR’s will be responsible for the following: Outbound cold calling to soliciting new accounts Building rapport with new prospects Providing technical information and explanations Delivering Webex presentations Preparing accurate quotes for customers Providing accurate forecast on a quarterly basis Attend industry conferences and events Closing new revenue in the range off $100K-$300K per quarter. Having fun! Desired Skills and Experience Qualifications Requirements:   Education & Experience: Bachelor’s Degree and 1+ year of high tech sales experience preferred.  Previous experience selling services in support of technology or software products is highly desirable but not required. Strong computer skills and knowledge of systems like SalesForce, NetSuite, Microsoft Products Fluent in Chinese Attention to detail and organizational skills Strong Presentation skills Ability to prioritize and meet deadlines Exhibited sales skills and track record of success Ability to use internal resources efficiently   Preferred Qualifications: Record of meeting and over-achieving monthly, quarterly and annual sales goals Experience managing diverse client base Closing Skills Prospecting Skills Technical understanding of enterprise network security products Record of building and maintaining customer (current and potential) relationships People Skills Data Entry SkillsAbout this companyTenable Network SecurityToday, modern enterprises face a plethora of technical, political, and business hurdles which make accurate security and compliance monitoring difficult and costly. Tenable has pioneered and continues to innovate a unique Unified Security Monitoring approach that is revolutionizing the way enterprises are monitoring (i.e. gathering, evaluating, communicating, and reporting) security and compliance information. Tenable Network Security is the pioneer and leader of Unified Security Monitoring. Tenable's award-winning products are agentless solutions and architected for the continuous monitoring of vulnerabilities, configurations, data leakage, log analysis and compromise detection and are used by thousands of organizations both large and small around the world. Although Tenable is known primarily for its Nessus vulnerability scanner product, Tenable's Unified Security Monitoring solution consists of four fully integrated software applications: Tenable's Security Center, Nessus, the Passive Vulnerability Scanner, and the Log Correlation Engine. An important strength of Tenable is the depth of security talent under one roof. Tenable's technical leaders have all created market leading and award winning products individually (Nessus, Dragon IDS, Guantlet Firewall, TIS firewall tool kit) prior to joining forces at Tenable. Tenable's Unified Security Monitoring approach is their combined vision on how to monitor and secure enterprise networks. Tenable was founded in September of 2002 and is privately held. Tenable's corporate offices are located in Columbia, Maryland.Other jobs at Tenable Network SecurityBaltimore, Maryland AreaJapanSingaporeSimilar jobsSingaporePosted 1 day agoSingaporePosted 8 days agoSingaporePosted 11 days agoSingaporePosted 11 hours agoSingaporePosted 1 day agoSingaporePosted 12 days agoSingaporePosted 8 days agoSingaporePosted 12 days agoSingaporePosted 12 days agoSingaporePosted 20 days agoThis is a preview of the Inside Sales Representative - Japan job at Tenable Network Security. To view the full job listing, join LinkedIn - its free!Join LinkedIn - its free!People also searchedPeople also viewedSingaporePosted 1 day agoSingaporePosted 8 days agoSingaporePosted 11 days agoSingaporePosted 11 hours agoSingaporePosted 1 day agoSingaporePosted 12 days agoSingaporePosted 8 days agoSingaporePosted 12 days agoSingaporePosted 12 days agoSingaporePosted 